# FORGE · Code Sandbox

> A zero-dependency, single-file HTML/CSS/JS sandbox with live preview, syntax highlighting, loop protection, and AI-powered code analysis.

---

## What is FORGE?

FORGE is a **self-contained code playground** — one HTML file, no build step, no dependencies, no CDN. Open it in any browser and start writing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript with instant live preview.

It was built to be the sandbox you'd actually want to use: fast, honest about what it does, and secure by default.

---

## Features

### Editor
- **Syntax highlighting** via a character-by-character tokenizer — no regex runs on already-transformed text, no broken nested spans
- **Line numbers** with color-coded gutter markers for code analysis results
- **Auto-indent** on Enter, detecting opening brackets
- **Smart brackets & quotes** — auto-close `{}`, `[]`, `()`, `""`, `''`, ` `` ` with cursor placement; skip over existing closing characters; wrap selections
- **Multi-line Tab / Shift+Tab** indentation
- **Ctrl+M** to toggle Tab between indentation and browser navigation
- **HTML tag autocomplete** — type `</` to auto-close the last open tag
- **Find & navigate** with match count, Prev/Next buttons, Enter/Shift+Enter, Escape to close
- **Go to line** — jump to any line number

### Preview & Safety
- **Live auto-run** with 850ms debounce (toggleable)
- **Ctrl+Enter** to run manually
- **Infinite loop protection** on two levels:
  - *Loop instrumentation* — `while`, `for`, and `do` bodies get an iteration counter injected before each run; throws after 2 million iterations
  - *Parent-thread watchdog* — monitors iframe heartbeats every 200ms; if the iframe thread freezes for >2s, the parent kills it from outside (the only approach that actually works for a blocked thread)
  - *Background-tab safe* — watchdog pauses when `document.hidden` to avoid false positives
- **iframe sandboxed** — `allow-scripts allow-modals allow-pointer-lock`, no `allow-same-origin` (prevents iframe from accessing parent storage or DOM)
- **postMessage origin check** — only accepts messages from the preview iframe

### Console
- Intercepts `console.log/warn/error/info` from the iframe via `postMessage`
- Catches `window.onerror` and `unhandledrejection`
- 200-line rolling buffer — no DOM flooding with AutoRun
- **Clear** button

### AI Code Analysis
- Click **🔍 Analyse** to send the current code to the Claude API
- Returns a structured list of issues with line numbers, severity (error / warning / info), message, and fix suggestion
- Issues appear in the **Analyse tab** — click any entry to jump to that line
- Gutter markers highlight affected line numbers in red / yellow / blue
- Markers clear automatically when you edit the code (results are stale)
- Works without configuration when used via [Claude.ai](https://claude.ai); for standalone use, enter your [Anthropic API key](https://console.anthropic.com) on first use (stored in `localStorage`, never transmitted anywhere else)

### Layout & UX
- **Split / vertical** layout toggle (⊞ button or swipe on panel headers)
- **Resizable console** — drag the handle between editor and console
- **Auto-save** to `localStorage` on every keystroke
- **AutoRun state** persisted across reloads
- Toast notifications for actions and errors
- Responsive — works on mobile (keyboard shortcuts adapt)

---

## Quick Start

**No installation. No build step.**

1. Download [`forge_sandbox_final.html`](forge_sandbox_final.html)
2. Open it in any modern browser
3. Start coding

That's it.

For **AI code analysis** without a Claude.ai account, add your Anthropic API key when prompted (or pre-set it in `localStorage` under the key `forge_api_key`).

